pageContext.claim: “The Democrats are talking, but they're never going to be able to do it because they can't get it through Congress, whereas I've gotten everything through Congress, whether it's criminal justice reform -- which everybody said couldn't be done, and many other things.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump most certainly has not “gotten everything” through Congress. His signature effort to repeal and replace the Affordable Care Act failed, despite Republicans having majorities in both the House of Representatives and the Senate.
